become a person
who doesn't even know what I like?

50
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:51,600
[Episode 5 "Someone I can like"]

51
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,933
Jin Woo, it was Jeong Gi Seop earlier, right?

52
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,533
How do you know him?

53
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:06,800
What is going on?

54
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:10,367
That bastard!

55
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:32,967
What are you doing?

56
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,133
Are you okay?

57
00:04:37,133 --> 00:04:38,333
Didn't you get hit?

58
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:41,633
Didn't Kang Hye Jin hit you?

59
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:42,667
What?

60
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:46,467
I mean, at the beginning of the semester…

61
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:50,467
No, what's going on right now?

62
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:51,800
What did she say?

63
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,600
Didn't she say something scary?

64
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,700
I didn't even know you two knew each other.

65
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,700
What?

66
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:03,200
Then, why were you two together?

67
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,033
- What?
- Do you know each other?

68
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,267
Kind of.

69
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:08,567
Are you two dating?

70
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,133
No, we're not.

71
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:18,267
It's nothing.

72
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:19,967
That's a relief.

73
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,200
No matter what happens,

74
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,300
I will protect you.

75
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:40,133
What is happening?

76
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:47,533
I met my perfect ideal type, but

77
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,567
all I could think of was Jeong Gi Seop.

78
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,000
What did you say?

79
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:11,633
I mean

80
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:14,067
what if Kang Hye Jin harasses Kim Jin Woo?

81
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:19,533
Well, since there is nothing between them,
I don't think they will meet again.

82
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:22,067
- No, it's not. 
 - What?

83
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:24,367
No, there is something between them.

84
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:28,200
I saw them coming out
of the theater while delivering.

85
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,567
- It looked like a date?
- No way.

86
00:06:30,567 --> 00:06:32,567
Kim Jin Woo wore a gray coat, right?

87
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:36,200
I think they both wore mufflers.

88
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,400
How did you know?

89
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,933
I think Kim Jin Woo was lying to you.

90
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,633
- No way.
- Then you mean I'm lying?

91
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:44,633
What?

92
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:46,767
That's not it.

93
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:47,767
- Hey.
- What?

94
00:06:47,767 --> 00:06:50,133
You like Kim Jin Woo, right?

95
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,333
If you like him, just confess it.
Why waste your energy?

96
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:59,000
- Do I like Kim Jin Woo? 
 - What?

97
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,967
I'm not capable of liking someone.

98
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:03,600
Why not? You have a lot of money.

99
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,800
Figure it out yourself.

100
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,367
I'm busy, so I'm off now.

101
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,633
- Delivery?
- No.

102
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:12,667
Then what?

103
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:14,267
I don't know.

104
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:16,033
What is he saying?

105
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:06,333
[- I want to go to your place.
- All right.]

106
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,867
[Ji In Ho]

107
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,700
- Hello? 
 - I think I'm almost there.

108
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:20,800
Oh, I'll go there now.

109
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,533
Hello.

110
00:08:34,467 --> 00:08:35,500
This is a present.

111
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:39,033
It's not a new house. Why did you buy this?

112
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:41,500
Thank you.

113
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:44,233
Let's go in.

114
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:51,533
Come in.

115
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,000
- I feel like…
- What?

116
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:09,367
Your house is too hot.

117
00:09:09,367 --> 00:09:13,467
I thought it's cold outside.
I'll lower it a little.

118
00:09:13,467 --> 00:09:14,933
Lower it a lot.

119
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:16,200
Where should I put this?

120
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,400
Oh, give it to me.

121
00:09:24,167 --> 00:09:25,200
Food will come soon.

122
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,333
What food?

123
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:32,600
Did you order it just for me?

124
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,867
Yeah.

125
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:36,400
I ordered various things.

126
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:38,667
This much?

127
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,300
Well, I just ordered plenty.

128
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:43,133
Try this, and try this.

129
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,200
It is so good.

130
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:46,867
Thank you. I will eat well.

131
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:53,367
[Korean University Book List]
[TOEIC regular test schedule]

132
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,733
[Checklist]
Taizong, Taizong of Tang, right?

133
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:58,067
[Silla's process of unification of the three kingdoms]
With the military support of Taizong of Tang,

134
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:59,500
they achieved results.

135
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:03,500
This is a new story
that says they have succeeded

136
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,367
in forming combined forces.

137
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:09,500
[Jeong Gi Seop]
You can select this period in the table.

138
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,200
[Jeong Gi Seop]
It's a question

139
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,400
of guessing why Taizong of Tang

140
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,933
approved Silla's proposal.

141
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:19,900
Now, the Goguryeo people…

142
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:28,933
Just a moment.

143
00:10:30,533 --> 00:10:32,433
Hello? Yes.

144
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:55,100
Why do you keep showing up?

145
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,633
You called me.

146
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:58,000
I didn't.

147
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,267
You just showed up.

148
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:01,967
Go, go away.

149
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,700
Do you really want me to go?

150
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:07,900
You want me to go away?

151
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:12,667
You want me to disappear
from your side forever?

152
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:17,800
No.

153
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:21,567
Don't do that.

154
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,833
[Jeong Gi Seop]

155
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,900
I'm so full.

156
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,600
You can stop eating.

157
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:07,367
Let's clean it together later.

158
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:09,067
Can't you take a short break too?

159
00:12:11,233 --> 00:12:12,367
All right.

160
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,900
Those are my socks.

161
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:36,033
What?

162
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,933
The socks got mixed up at that time.

163
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,667
You don't wear them anyway.

164
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:42,933
I couldn't throw it away.

165
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,600
You threw my socks away, right?

166
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,467
How can I throw that away?

167
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:51,067
They're at my home.

168
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:54,167
Why didn't you throw them away?
Throw away the worn-out stuff.

169
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:57,333
I was about to throw them away too.
Because they're too old.

170
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:58,867
I'll bring them to you

171
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:01,400
when we meet three times later.

172
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,133
I wanted to try this.

173
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:14,967
What?

174
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,267
Doing nothing

175
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,700
and just being together.

176
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:20,733
It's not that special.

177
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:25,167
Can we keep doing this today?

178
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,067
You don't like it? Should we go outside?

179
00:13:31,067 --> 00:13:32,067
Both work for me.

180
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:34,033
Do whatever you want.

181
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,467
Then…

182
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:40,467
Let's do what you want next time.

183
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:43,333
That's what I want.

184
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,367
But the room is too small, right?

185
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:47,133
I'll get some plastic bags.

186
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:49,700
Oh, I need to clean it up. The room is small.

187
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:52,767
I like this place.

188
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,367
I like it.

189
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,867
You came on behalf of Balgeum, right?

190
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,267
Yes.

191
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:13,467
Balgeum's friend.

192
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,633
Are you already absent-minded?

193
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:18,467
You wore it inside out.

194
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:19,633
You're

195
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:21,733
really handsome.

196
00:14:21,733 --> 00:14:24,767
Sales haven't gone up for a few days,

197
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:27,200
so please pay attention to sales today.

198
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,233
- Okay?
- Yes.

199
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:29,533
- Keep it up.
- Yes.

200
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:40,000
Balgeum's friend.

201
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,433
Your good looks are very helpful today.

202
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:44,900
There are really a lot of orders.

203
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,267
Hello.

204
00:14:47,267 --> 00:14:49,167
Hello, would you like to order?

205
00:14:49,167 --> 00:14:52,133
Is there anything you can recommend?

206
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,067
I don't know much, either.

207
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:01,300
You're so funny. How could you not know?

208
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,533
He's so funny.

209
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:04,167
Would you like chicken noodles?

210
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,100
Yes, three please.

211
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:11,733
Hello.

212
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:13,933
Did you say hello?

213
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:19,700
How do you know Jin Woo?

214
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:24,000
Then, how do you know Jin Woo?

215
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:26,567
Can't you see it?

216
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:31,667
[Jin Woo's Ideal Type Checklist]
I'm his ideal type.

217
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:33,500
He is my ideal type.

218
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:41,500
Do you understand?

219
00:15:42,367 --> 00:15:43,733
No way.

220
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:46,333
What are you doing to Kim Jin Woo?

221
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,933
I'll be perfect for his ideal type
and Kim Jin Woo will also…

222
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:55,433
You're still the same

223
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:57,900
at playing with people's sincerity.

224
00:15:59,533 --> 00:16:02,800
What's happening?

225
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:03,867
Well…

226
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,167
Oh, I'm sorry.

227
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:09,800
I'm sorry.

228
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,867
Well.

229
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:14,967
This is the guy who cheated on me
with my ex-girlfriend and ex-boyfriend.

230
00:16:14,967 --> 00:16:17,533
And he even two-timed them.

231
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,100
Please don't do this here.

232
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,300
I'm sorry, sorry.

233
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:32,200
Are you leaving?

234
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,500
You don't think Jin Woo

235
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,667
really likes you, right?

236
00:17:07,533 --> 00:17:10,333
[Kang Hye Jin, I have something to say.
Can I see you for a second?]

237
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,300
Jeong Gi Seop.

238
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,700
Do you know what you have to do for Jin Woo?

239
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:30,767
What is that?

240
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:33,500
Stop playing weird

241
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:37,067
and just disappear from his sight.

242
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:40,767
Please don't hurt him
like you did to my friends.

243
00:17:42,033 --> 00:17:43,900
You don't even really like him.

244
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:57,000
[Kang Hye Jin, I have something to say.
Can I see you for a second?]

245
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,333
I'm leaving.

246
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:03,500
Let's not run into each other again.

247
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:10,533
I'll take your orders from now on.

248
00:18:10,533 --> 00:18:12,700
What would you like to order?

249
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:17,633
Please choose one. It's good.

250
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,333
[Jin Woo]

251
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:42,300
The subscriber you are calling
is not available…

252
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,833
Balgeum's friend, are you all right?

253
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:11,567
No, I'm not.

254
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:14,233
You need to cheer up.

255
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,933
We need to get more customers.

256
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,567
[Korea Amendment Act
Application has been rejected]

257
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,167
I have somewhere to go.

258
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,200
Balgeum's friend.

259
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:37,300
I need to check now

260
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:40,900
that I can never be your ideal type

261
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,300
and that I really can't like you.

262
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,133
Jin Woo.

263
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,833
I didn't know you would contact me first?

264
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,967
What do you have to say?

265
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:11,500
This.

266
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,833
I think I should show it to you.

267
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:33,267
[Jeong Gi Seop XXXX]
I wrote it down like a diary.

268
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,733
But he read it all.

269
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:51,100
When did you first write this?

270
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,567
I think it was the day I first met him.

271
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:55,767
When I got home.

